<p>All this does is <code>json_decode</code> the request body and call <code>$form-&gt;submit()</code>. That
does the same thing as <code>$form-&gt;handleRequest()</code>, which you're probably familiar with.
So after this function is called, the form processing has happened. After it, add
an <code>if</code> statement with the normal <code>if (!$form-&gt;isValid())</code>:</p>
