<p>If we find ourselves here, it means we have validation errors. Let's see if this
is working. Use the <code>dump()</code> function and the <code>$form-&gt;getErrors()</code> function, passing
it <code>true</code> and <code>false</code> as arguments. That'll give us all the errors in a big tree.
Cast this to a string - <code>getErrors()</code> returns a <code>FormErrorIterator</code> object, which
has a nice <code>__toString()</code> method. Add a <code>die</code> at the end:</p>
