</p>
<p>Remember, we want <code>type</code>, <code>title</code> and <code>errors</code> keys. Add a <code>type</code> key: this is the
machine name of what went wrong. How about <code>validation_error</code> - I'm making that up.
For <code>title</code> - we'll have the human-readable version of what went wrong. Let's use:
"There was a validation error". And for <code>errors</code> pass it the <code>$errors</code> array.</p>
<p>Finish it off! Return a <code>new JsonResponse()</code> with <code>$data</code> <em>and</em> the 400 status code:</p>
